What you're saying is it was Lee Hyeong-du
20 years ago...

259
00:15:51,920 --> 00:15:53,480
who called out Professor Hwang...

260
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:54,800
and caused a problem.

261
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,160
Yes, that's right.

262
00:15:56,160 --> 00:15:58,440
You mean it was Lee Hyeong-du...

263
00:15:58,440 --> 00:16:00,080
who also recently abducted
Professor Hwang, right?

264
00:16:00,400 --> 00:16:03,760
Yes. I'll hand in the related evidence.

265
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:07,800
Also, I'll also forward you
other reference materials...

266
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:09,680
I couldn't fit into the 55-minute runtime.

267
00:16:26,200 --> 00:16:29,560
(Bureau Chief, Na Ha-young)

268
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:40,640
I'm running out of time.

269
00:16:41,480 --> 00:16:42,560
Please help me.

270
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:45,480
(Why must I...)

271
00:16:46,520 --> 00:16:48,760
(get shook up over a single word
from you?)

272
00:16:50,560 --> 00:16:52,400
(When you asked me for help,)

273
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:55,800
(I shattered to pieces,
and I lost ground.)

274
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:56,880
(Why am I like this?)

275
00:16:58,560 --> 00:16:59,720
(Ma Dong-chan.)

276
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:03,600
(I want to free myself from you.)

277
00:17:15,560 --> 00:17:17,960
Why did you do that?

278
00:17:19,599 --> 00:17:21,560
I couldn't stand it.

279
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:24,880
I was constantly going in
and out of prison,

280
00:17:25,599 --> 00:17:28,920
while you were recognized by Father
when you met him later.

281
00:17:30,520 --> 00:17:32,040
That's why I thought...

282
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:35,560
I should become Lee Seok-du.

283
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:39,240
I decided to steal
Lee Seok-du's life whole.

284
00:17:39,680 --> 00:17:40,680
Hyeong-du.

285
00:17:40,680 --> 00:17:42,400
That night 21 years ago,

286
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:45,240
I thought I got rid of you.

287
00:17:48,560 --> 00:17:49,560
Honey!

288
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:56,200
(The only people who could
give you blood...)

289
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:58,040
(were me and Jung-woo
since you're a rare type.)

290
00:17:58,400 --> 00:17:59,960
(Jung-woo was too young then,)

291
00:17:59,960 --> 00:18:01,720
(so it'd be too dangerous for him
to give you blood.)

292
00:18:03,120 --> 00:18:04,920
(I thought you'd die...)

293
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:07,720
(as long as I didn't show up.)

294
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:12,680
(I never imagined Mother and your wife...)

295
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:16,160
(would put you inside a cryonic capsule
as you were dying.)

296
00:18:20,760 --> 00:18:22,320
It was still fine...

297
00:18:22,960 --> 00:18:25,920
because I was already Lee Seok-du.

298
00:18:26,480 --> 00:18:27,520
But,

299
00:18:28,520 --> 00:18:31,960
when Ma Dong-chan woke up,

300
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:34,600
everything got messy.

301
00:18:37,040 --> 00:18:38,160
You people...

302
00:18:39,400 --> 00:18:42,040
should have stayed frozen forever.

303
00:18:52,360 --> 00:18:54,520
Dong-chan just arrived at the station.

304
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:55,560
Really?

305
00:18:57,960 --> 00:18:59,240
-You're cool.
-You're cool.

306
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:03,240
-Hello.
-Hi.

307
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:15,320
Today's lunch is Chinese food.
I'll take your orders.

308
00:19:15,600 --> 00:19:17,400
-I'll have japchae on rice.
-I'll have jjamppong.

309
00:19:18,320 --> 00:19:19,600
Can we order sharing dishes?

310
00:19:20,280 --> 00:19:21,800
-I'll have fried rice.
-I'll have a jjajangmyeon.

311
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:23,240
One jjajangmyeon.

312
00:19:33,720 --> 00:19:36,160
(Should I eat jjamppong or jjajangmyeon?)

313
00:19:38,080 --> 00:19:39,120
(Jjajangmyeon.)

314
00:19:42,960 --> 00:19:45,520
Mr. Ma, I sent you the file.

315
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:46,600
Okay.

316
00:19:56,720 --> 00:20:00,080
(Should I print that file or look at it
on my monitor?)

317
00:20:13,760 --> 00:20:15,400
(I'm going to go to the washroom.)

318
00:20:15,840 --> 00:20:18,040
(Should I go to the 2nd floor
or the 3rd floor?)

319
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:35,720
Are you rebelling?

320
00:20:36,280 --> 00:20:38,440
This isn't the kind of discussion
I was referring to.

321
00:20:40,600 --> 00:20:41,800
Why aren't you talking?

322
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:44,960
Should I be honest or should I be nice?

323
00:20:45,080 --> 00:20:47,640
Don't ask me. Don't discuss with me.
Figure it out on your own.

324
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:56,320
You told me not to ask you, so...

325
00:20:59,120 --> 00:21:00,400
What was that?

326
00:21:20,600 --> 00:21:22,640
-Be honest.
-I'm telling you the truth.

327
00:21:22,640 --> 00:21:23,720
Sure.

328
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:27,880
What? What?

329
00:21:28,080 --> 00:21:29,640
We're dating. So what?

330
00:21:32,320 --> 00:21:34,840
-Are you in love?
-Gosh.

331
00:21:35,040 --> 00:21:37,920
I shouldn't have told everyone I know...

332
00:21:37,920 --> 00:21:40,160
that I'm close with Lee Seok-du.

333
00:21:40,160 --> 00:21:42,640
He wasn't Lee Seok-du,
he was Lee Hyeong-du.

334
00:21:42,840 --> 00:21:44,600
You were rooked.

335
00:21:45,600 --> 00:21:47,960
How can something more dramatic
than a drama happen to me?

336
00:21:48,160 --> 00:21:50,000
I'm now free from all this,

337
00:21:50,120 --> 00:21:52,080
but you must be worried.

338
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:56,960
What is this? Are you two together again?

339
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:01,880
You should just get married
if you want to be this close.

340
00:22:03,080 --> 00:22:05,440
What... What brings you here?

341
00:22:05,640 --> 00:22:08,000
We should wrap things up.
I made a broadcasting accident.

342
00:22:08,480 --> 00:22:11,000
Should I get fired or should I hand
in my resignation?

343
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:14,720
I'm not sure. What should we do?

344
00:22:16,120 --> 00:22:18,080
By the way, when do you plan
on getting fired?

345
00:22:18,320 --> 00:22:19,720
-Why should I get fired?
-You partnered with...

346
00:22:19,720 --> 00:22:21,000
the fake Lee Seok-du
and did all kinds of things.

347
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:24,600
I didn't! He and I parted ways.

348
00:22:25,120 --> 00:22:27,280
Please. Just leave on your own.

349
00:22:27,640 --> 00:22:28,640
I don't want to.

350
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:30,960
Anyway, here's my resignation letter.

351
00:22:31,640 --> 00:22:32,680
(Resignation Letter)

352
00:22:32,680 --> 00:22:36,200
Hey, why are you suddenly resigning?

353
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:40,320
Hey! Let's go out to eat.

354
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:42,640
I don't want to.

355
00:22:42,640 --> 00:22:43,640
(Ma Dong-chan)

356
00:22:44,320 --> 00:22:46,000
Hey, Dong-chan. Dong-chan!

357
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:48,600
You can't just... Hey!

358
00:22:51,040 --> 00:22:52,480
You handed in a resignation letter...

359
00:22:53,120 --> 00:22:54,640
without even telling me?

360
00:22:54,840 --> 00:22:55,880
Yes.

361
00:22:56,360 --> 00:22:58,080
You told me I didn't have to discuss
everything with you.

362
00:22:58,080 --> 00:23:00,280
Why are you always so extreme?

363
00:23:02,640 --> 00:23:04,680
Hey, don't get angry.

364
00:23:04,680 --> 00:23:06,120
Your body temperature will rise.

365
00:23:07,240 --> 00:23:09,000
Do you have a plan?

366
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,320
Yes, my niece told me I should start
a Youtube channel.

367
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:13,040
You never listen to anyone.

368
00:23:13,040 --> 00:23:14,320
But you listen to your niece?

369
00:23:14,320 --> 00:23:16,720
Yes, I always listen to her.
She's very smart.

370
00:23:17,320 --> 00:23:18,520
So I've been thinking.

371
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:21,040
How about we both quit...

372
00:23:21,040 --> 00:23:22,680
and start a Youtube channel together?

373
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:27,400
These days, TV isn't the mainstream media.

374
00:23:28,040 --> 00:23:29,760
So let's both quit...

375
00:23:29,760 --> 00:23:31,160
and start our own channel.

376
00:23:31,280 --> 00:23:33,600
How long are you going
to work as an intern?

377
00:23:35,560 --> 00:23:37,120
I'm not sure.

378
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:39,440
-Well...
-Yes?

379
00:23:40,120 --> 00:23:42,320
Maybe it's because I'm old-fashioned,

380
00:23:42,320 --> 00:23:43,960
but I still think...

381
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:45,880
TV shows are the most influential.

382
00:23:46,040 --> 00:23:48,440
Plus, I already asked for
a chance on social media.

383
00:23:49,560 --> 00:23:51,680
And more importantly,
at least one of us...

384
00:23:51,680 --> 00:23:53,160
should have a stable income.

385
00:23:53,160 --> 00:23:54,840
You're going to stay
at a broadcasting station...

386
00:23:54,840 --> 00:23:56,720
where Ma Dong-chan no longer exists?

387
00:23:56,720 --> 00:23:58,280
But work is work.

388
00:23:58,360 --> 00:24:00,200
So you just expect me to quit
and leave you...

389
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:01,760
to work with that young intern?

390
00:24:01,760 --> 00:24:03,200
No way! I can't do that!

391
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:05,280
Come on. You should quit as well.

392
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:10,440
You can't get what you want just
by whining like this.

393
00:24:10,560 --> 00:24:13,200
You can quit by yourself.

394
00:24:14,880 --> 00:24:16,040
You're so cold-hearted.

395
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:20,440
I guess you're cold
because you're a cryonic.

396
00:24:20,480 --> 00:24:23,040
I don't need a job there.
I'm just going to stay here.

397
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:25,800
What used to bother me here is no longer
a problem.

398
00:24:26,120 --> 00:24:30,120
And the broadcasting station keeps
asking me to stay.

399
00:24:30,960 --> 00:24:33,680
What? You didn't have a vacant spot
for me anyway?

400
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:36,600
I don't intend to work there either!

401
00:24:38,280 --> 00:24:40,280
The actual first episode of "Go Go 99"...

402
00:24:40,320 --> 00:24:43,600
will air this weekend, so keep
that in mind.

403
00:24:44,320 --> 00:24:45,440
And one more thing.

404
00:24:48,240 --> 00:24:50,320
Director Ma,
the legendary variety show director...

405
00:24:50,480 --> 00:24:54,240
whom we can't live without will be
leaving us now.

406
00:24:56,080 --> 00:24:57,640
It hurts me so much.

407
00:24:58,240 --> 00:24:59,800
But we should still let him go.

408
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:02,400
Sir.

409
00:25:02,400 --> 00:25:05,280
Did he get fired or decide to quit
on his own?

410
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:07,280
He obviously got fired because
of what he did.

411
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:10,080
If any of you run into him,

412
00:25:10,080 --> 00:25:12,760
-show him your condolences.
-What are you talking about?

413
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:14,080
I'm not dead.

414
00:25:15,880 --> 00:25:17,880
Plus, I'm the one who decided to quit.

415
00:25:17,880 --> 00:25:19,640
No one has the right to fire me.

416
00:25:19,640 --> 00:25:21,280
I'm Ma Dong-chan.

417
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:26,280
Everyone.

418
00:25:26,760 --> 00:25:29,120
I'll be leaving as of today.

419
00:25:29,760 --> 00:25:31,320
I'm 52 years old,

420
00:25:31,320 --> 00:25:34,080
and I know I may be too old
to start something new.

421
00:25:34,360 --> 00:25:35,840
But I'm still going to give it a try.

422
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:38,080
I should do something no one else has
ever done before...

423
00:25:38,080 --> 00:25:39,440
in order to change this world.

424
00:25:44,160 --> 00:25:45,840
Hey, what are you doing?

425
00:25:47,360 --> 00:25:51,080
I wanted to help you pack since
it's your last day here.

426
00:25:51,240 --> 00:25:53,760
I'll pack everything so
that you won't have to return.

427
00:25:56,160 --> 00:25:57,440
That punk.

428
00:25:59,480 --> 00:26:00,560
Mi-ran.

429
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:03,840
I'm having trouble with this.

430
00:26:03,920 --> 00:26:06,440
Oh, this? I've done this before,
and it's not that hard.

431
00:26:06,840 --> 00:26:08,080
-Oh, really?
-Yes.

432
00:26:08,080 --> 00:26:09,480
Have you tried doing this?

433
00:26:09,480 --> 00:26:10,600
Yes, I have.

434
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:13,120
Hey, stop asking her questions...

435
00:26:13,120 --> 00:26:15,800
and just read the book.
It's all written in the book.

436
00:26:15,800 --> 00:26:18,360
You'll learn a lot from it.

437
00:26:30,200 --> 00:26:31,960
My gosh, I'm tired.

438
00:26:49,880 --> 00:26:51,320
("Go Go 99")

439
00:26:53,560 --> 00:26:56,080
(A DDR machine takes them back in time.
Dong-sik falls down.)

440
00:26:56,080 --> 00:26:57,400
That's me.

441
00:26:57,520 --> 00:26:58,760
Are you okay?

442
00:26:59,080 --> 00:27:00,760
-(Bottoms up!)
-(Bottoms up!)

443
00:27:00,760 --> 00:27:02,320
-(Bottoms up!)
-(I'll drink.)

444
00:27:02,520 --> 00:27:04,760
So that's what I look on TV.

445
00:27:04,760 --> 00:27:06,560
(She finishes her glass.)

446
00:27:06,840 --> 00:27:08,480
That's what I'm talking about.

447
00:27:08,800 --> 00:27:11,480
(Age is just a tool to maintain
a hierarchical culture.)

448
00:27:11,480 --> 00:27:13,600
(It's not something that defines you.)

449
00:27:14,160 --> 00:27:16,080
(Forget about your age...)

450
00:27:16,080 --> 00:27:18,160
(and start living a happy life
like Peter Pan.)

451
00:27:18,160 --> 00:27:19,920
(Bravo your life!)

452
00:27:20,640 --> 00:27:23,560
My dream as a child

453
00:27:23,880 --> 00:27:27,080
Was to ride a yellow balloon

454
00:27:28,040 --> 00:27:31,800
And fly high up in the sky

455
00:27:31,800 --> 00:27:34,720
It took six hours to film my interview.

456
00:27:34,720 --> 00:27:36,880
How could you only air two minutes of it?

457
00:27:36,880 --> 00:27:38,640
Where are you going to use...

458
00:27:38,640 --> 00:27:42,000
the remaining footage of 58 minutes?

459
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:43,560
I won't let this slide.

460
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:46,320
Hey, you fake 52-year-old.

461
00:27:46,320 --> 00:27:48,400
I'm not someone you can mess with.

462
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:53,040
("A Variety Show on a Public TV Channel
Hits 21.3 Percent")

463
00:27:55,080 --> 00:27:57,320
("Director Ma Returns
With Another Hit Show, 'Go Go 99'")

464
00:27:57,400 --> 00:27:59,480
("'Go Go 99' Has the Highest Number
of Downloads")

465
00:27:59,640 --> 00:28:00,880
("'Go Go 99' Has the Highest Number
of Downloads")

466
00:28:01,040 --> 00:28:04,760
("Where Is the Genius Director,
Ma Dong-chan?")

467
00:28:19,480 --> 00:28:20,720
Where's Mom?

468
00:28:21,720 --> 00:28:23,800
She went to church.

469
00:28:23,800 --> 00:28:26,760
You got yourself in trouble
and became jobless.

470
00:28:26,760 --> 00:28:29,640
So she thinks she should do something
to help as a mother.

471
00:28:31,800 --> 00:28:33,280
Uncle, what's your plan for today?

472
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:34,440
Me?

473
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:37,440
I'm going to go to the library.

474
00:28:37,440 --> 00:28:38,720
You went there yesterday.

475
00:28:38,960 --> 00:28:41,480
Everything in the library is all
on the internet.

476
00:28:41,560 --> 00:28:43,960
Don't waste your energy like that.
You're already old enough.

477
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:46,920
To be honest,

478
00:28:47,240 --> 00:28:50,720
I'm thinking of starting
a Youtube channel tomorrow.

479
00:28:50,760 --> 00:28:52,800
Yes, let's talk about that.

480
00:28:53,120 --> 00:28:54,320
What kind of content are you going
to make?

481
00:28:54,320 --> 00:28:57,120
Beauty? Eating shows? Games? ASMR?

482
00:28:58,160 --> 00:29:00,640
How about a beauty channel?
Are you okay with wearing makeup?

483
00:29:00,720 --> 00:29:02,080
Makeup?

484
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:03,520
Why would I put makeup on my face?

485
00:29:04,320 --> 00:29:08,360
I lived longer than you,
so let me give you some advice.

486
00:29:10,440 --> 00:29:11,560
Listen to me carefully!

487
00:29:13,600 --> 00:29:16,080
You're free to do everything you want
to do in life.

488
00:29:16,200 --> 00:29:18,880
But you should also know
that life is very precious.

489
00:29:19,680 --> 00:29:23,720
You should think of living a long
and stable life.

490
00:29:24,360 --> 00:29:26,520
Even if you have to go through a lot,

491
00:29:26,520 --> 00:29:28,960
it's still better to live than to die.

492
00:29:29,960 --> 00:29:31,280
So please...

493
00:29:31,280 --> 00:29:33,400
don't risk your life on anything.

494
00:29:34,880 --> 00:29:37,800
She's right. I also want
to live a long life.

495
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:39,800
I want to live as long as possible.

496
00:29:39,800 --> 00:29:43,200
I want my life to be very long and stable.

497
00:29:44,440 --> 00:29:46,040
A living crab...

498
00:29:46,040 --> 00:29:48,760
is better than a dead Napoleon.

499
00:29:55,320 --> 00:29:58,720
It's never bad to listen to someone
who's more experienced in life.

500
00:30:05,480 --> 00:30:08,400
As we all expected,
"Go Go 99" did great on TV.

501
00:30:08,600 --> 00:30:10,960
I think it's going to get added
to the official schedule.

502
00:30:10,960 --> 00:30:12,400
-Nice!
-Great!

503
00:30:12,400 --> 00:30:14,840
-You did great.
-Good job.

504
00:30:14,840 --> 00:30:16,760
It's been a while. Good work.

505
00:30:18,440 --> 00:30:19,520
What is it?

506
00:30:21,040 --> 00:30:24,400
What are you doing here?
I thought you quit.

507
00:30:24,680 --> 00:30:25,880
I just came.

508
00:30:26,040 --> 00:30:29,360
By the way, where's Mi-ran
and the other intern?

509
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:31,440
Mi-ran went to cast the guests
for our show.

510
00:30:31,920 --> 00:30:33,880
-And the intern?
-I'm not sure.

511
00:30:34,280 --> 00:30:36,320
I think he went with Mi-ran.

512
00:30:36,840 --> 00:30:38,840
Why? Why would he go with her?

513
00:30:42,280 --> 00:30:44,360
Mi-ran, aren't you hungry?

514
00:30:44,600 --> 00:30:45,880
Are you hungry?

515
00:30:46,080 --> 00:30:47,160
A little?

516
00:30:47,280 --> 00:30:50,120
I can't let you stay hungry.
