00:44:23,240 --> 00:44:24,360
Professor Hwang.

775
00:44:27,880 --> 00:44:29,880
You're going to get busy now.

776
00:44:30,280 --> 00:44:32,040
Many things will happen to you.

777
00:44:33,120 --> 00:44:36,000
I'm sure since Lee Seok-du is awake.

778
00:44:36,200 --> 00:44:37,600
Things will change.

779
00:44:37,600 --> 00:44:39,280
You'll get busy too.

780
00:44:39,280 --> 00:44:42,080
You promised me 20 years ago saying...

781
00:44:42,560 --> 00:44:45,000
you'd help me succeed
with the cryonics experiment...

782
00:44:45,520 --> 00:44:48,840
with only Korean funds and technology.

783
00:44:49,760 --> 00:44:51,600
Yes, I did.

784
00:44:51,720 --> 00:44:53,520
I think it'll be realized soon.

785
00:44:54,600 --> 00:44:57,440
We just need to bring back
your normal body temperature.

786
00:44:57,880 --> 00:45:01,000
As long as we get that resolved,
then this experiment is a success.

787
00:45:01,640 --> 00:45:03,840
You did it.

788
00:45:04,880 --> 00:45:06,280
It's only the beginning.

789
00:45:06,640 --> 00:45:07,920
By the way,

790
00:45:09,200 --> 00:45:12,560
when can we start living
like ordinary people?

791
00:45:14,000 --> 00:45:15,120
Soon.

792
00:45:35,760 --> 00:45:36,800
(What are you doing?)

793
00:45:40,200 --> 00:45:41,400
(I'm about to go to bed.)

794
00:45:43,680 --> 00:45:45,600
(How can you be sleepy when I'm upstairs?)

795
00:45:45,600 --> 00:45:47,000
(How can you be sleepy when I'm upstairs?)

796
00:45:47,000 --> 00:45:48,080
(Giggling)

797
00:45:48,320 --> 00:45:49,840
(Don't just giggle.)

798
00:45:50,080 --> 00:45:52,120
(Don't just giggle.)

799
00:45:52,120 --> 00:45:53,480
(Should I go up?)

800
00:45:55,400 --> 00:45:57,280
(Should I go up?)

801
00:46:09,640 --> 00:46:12,200
It's a little hot up here.
Will you be okay?

802
00:46:12,200 --> 00:46:13,400
I missed you.

803
00:46:15,200 --> 00:46:16,320
Me too.

804
00:46:54,280 --> 00:46:56,600
Hey. Hey, what were you thinking?

805
00:46:56,600 --> 00:46:57,840
You had naughty thoughts,
didn't you?

806
00:46:57,840 --> 00:47:01,120
What do you mean?
Yours started ringing faster.

807
00:47:01,280 --> 00:47:02,640
What were you thinking?

808
00:47:04,600 --> 00:47:06,760
Hey, we should...

809
00:47:07,960 --> 00:47:09,040
go outside.

810
00:47:09,160 --> 00:47:12,360
This place isn't a good idea.

811
00:47:13,080 --> 00:47:14,360
Go where?

812
00:47:15,520 --> 00:47:17,760
Anyway, we shouldn't stay here.

813
00:47:17,760 --> 00:47:18,800
Let's go out.

814
00:47:20,360 --> 00:47:21,640
It's so hot.

815
00:47:32,840 --> 00:47:34,640
I wish our temperatures
would return fast...

816
00:47:34,640 --> 00:47:36,720
so we could do everything other people do.

817
00:47:37,520 --> 00:47:38,560
Me too.

818
00:47:38,560 --> 00:47:40,760
I wish it could feel cold in here.

819
00:47:41,240 --> 00:47:42,520
Me too.

820
00:47:42,640 --> 00:47:45,520
I want to drink a hot americano
within five minutes.

821
00:47:45,600 --> 00:47:46,920
Me too.

822
00:47:47,080 --> 00:47:48,760
I want to love you like crazy.

823
00:47:49,600 --> 00:47:50,640
Me too.

824
00:47:51,280 --> 00:47:53,760
Instead of just agreeing with me,

825
00:47:53,760 --> 00:47:55,160
say what you want too.

826
00:47:56,840 --> 00:48:00,280
Earmuffs. Fur hats. Leggings.

827
00:48:00,720 --> 00:48:02,520
I want to wear long boots.

828
00:48:02,680 --> 00:48:03,720
Me too.

829
00:48:05,240 --> 00:48:07,000
Gosh, it's cold.

830
00:48:08,560 --> 00:48:12,120
-I'm dizzy.
-Gosh, this place is crazy.

831
00:48:12,120 --> 00:48:13,720
Hey, look at that.

832
00:48:14,440 --> 00:48:15,840
I can't stay here. Let's go.

833
00:48:15,840 --> 00:48:17,600
Yes, let's go.

834
00:48:20,080 --> 00:48:22,160
It's an ice room, so it's cold.

835
00:48:22,840 --> 00:48:24,960
How can they stay there?

836
00:48:24,960 --> 00:48:26,920
Hey, a drama is starting.

837
00:48:28,720 --> 00:48:29,760
Let's watch it.

838
00:48:30,400 --> 00:48:33,600
(The talk of buying out
the electronics company...)

839
00:48:33,640 --> 00:48:35,240
-Gosh.
-It finished.

840
00:48:35,240 --> 00:48:37,880
Hey, do you want to go to
the ice room again?

841
00:48:38,080 --> 00:48:39,720
-It's hot, so why don't we go?
-Okay.

842
00:48:40,520 --> 00:48:42,240
Should we have another drink?

843
00:48:43,840 --> 00:48:45,280
Were they in here all this time?

844
00:48:45,720 --> 00:48:48,200
-That's crazy.
-They're amazing.

845
00:48:48,200 --> 00:48:50,360
(Serious Crimes Team 2)

846
00:48:50,360 --> 00:48:51,360
Let's see.

847
00:48:52,680 --> 00:48:54,800
(Murder Suspect Wanted)

848
00:49:09,120 --> 00:49:10,600
(I just finished getting ready.)

849
00:49:16,720 --> 00:49:18,520
(I just finished getting ready.)

850
00:49:18,520 --> 00:49:19,720
(I'm heading out too.)

851
00:49:20,000 --> 00:49:21,720
(See you outside in three minutes.)

852
00:49:21,720 --> 00:49:23,760
(See you outside in three minutes.)

853
00:49:29,120 --> 00:49:31,240
Hello.

854
00:49:31,240 --> 00:49:32,240
I'll be back.

855
00:49:32,240 --> 00:49:34,040
Where are you going?

856
00:49:34,040 --> 00:49:35,440
You should have breakfast.

857
00:49:35,800 --> 00:49:37,400
I normally don't eat breakfast.

858
00:49:37,400 --> 00:49:38,680
Just sit down.

859
00:49:38,680 --> 00:49:39,800
Let's eat together.

860
00:49:39,800 --> 00:49:41,440
-Yes. Here.
-Sit down.

861
00:49:43,120 --> 00:49:45,480
Gosh. Thank you for the food.

862
00:49:45,840 --> 00:49:48,880
This is the spoon the professor used
to use.

863
00:49:48,880 --> 00:49:50,680
I see. "Professor"?

864
00:49:50,720 --> 00:49:53,440
There was a professor
who lived in the rooftop house.

865
00:49:54,960 --> 00:49:56,080
I miss him.

866
00:49:57,640 --> 00:49:59,640
Do you mean Professor Hwang?

867
00:50:00,160 --> 00:50:03,160
I wonder if he's doing well.

868
00:50:12,960 --> 00:50:14,800
Then that rooftop house...

869
00:50:14,800 --> 00:50:17,840
is a place where all the men related
to you stay.

870
00:50:18,000 --> 00:50:19,840
What's with you this time?

871
00:50:20,600 --> 00:50:22,920
He moved in without my permission.

872
00:50:23,240 --> 00:50:24,240
Gosh.

873
00:50:25,360 --> 00:50:26,520
Are you upset?

874
00:50:26,520 --> 00:50:29,720
What's there to be upset about?
It's just funny.

875
00:50:31,400 --> 00:50:33,680
That professor is really something.

876
00:50:33,840 --> 00:50:35,680
How could he move in?

877
00:50:35,760 --> 00:50:38,000
Also, same with that young intern.

878
00:50:38,000 --> 00:50:39,880
I heard his mom is your friend.

879
00:50:40,000 --> 00:50:41,040
Yes, she is.

880
00:50:42,000 --> 00:50:44,840
Her husband is Hwang Byung-sim.

881
00:50:44,840 --> 00:50:46,000
I see.

882
00:50:47,400 --> 00:50:49,320
I said, his dad is Hwang Byung-sim.

883
00:50:49,320 --> 00:50:50,400
I heard you.

884
00:50:50,680 --> 00:50:51,840
What? What?

885
00:50:53,240 --> 00:50:55,520
That young intern's dad is
Hwang Byung-sim?

886
00:50:58,280 --> 00:51:01,000
Gosh, what's with that family?

887
00:51:01,760 --> 00:51:04,320
Gosh. How...

888
00:51:14,640 --> 00:51:16,880
They say this ice room is really romantic.

889
00:51:16,880 --> 00:51:18,200
Let's go here next time.

890
00:51:20,400 --> 00:51:22,600
Thank you for the ride. See you later.

891
00:51:28,520 --> 00:51:29,760
Why did you get off?

892
00:51:30,240 --> 00:51:31,320
I can do whatever I want.

893
00:51:35,280 --> 00:51:37,720
-Yes. Work hard.
-Okay.

894
00:51:38,320 --> 00:51:39,840
-Hello.
-Hello.

895
00:51:40,040 --> 00:51:41,360
You should work hard.

896
00:51:42,480 --> 00:51:44,440
You should always work hard.

897
00:51:46,960 --> 00:51:48,960
What are you doing here again?

898
00:51:49,640 --> 00:51:51,000
-I came because I wanted to.
-Why did you even bother...

899
00:51:51,000 --> 00:51:53,120
to quit in the first place?

900
00:51:53,560 --> 00:51:55,240
You come here more often than you used to.

901
00:51:55,240 --> 00:51:56,800
None of that is your concern.

902
00:52:00,280 --> 00:52:03,120
Dong-chan, do you know that Ha-young quit?

903
00:52:06,760 --> 00:52:09,560
(Unsung Group)

904
00:52:09,560 --> 00:52:11,880
After the world found out that
Lee Hyeong-du was a fake,

905
00:52:12,000 --> 00:52:14,120
Unsung Group's stock price
keeps plummeting.

906
00:52:14,480 --> 00:52:15,600
I'm doomed.

907
00:52:16,040 --> 00:52:17,800
I bought a ton of their stocks
because I was told it'll rise.

908
00:52:18,160 --> 00:52:21,720
By the way, are you sure Dong-chan quit?

909
00:52:22,120 --> 00:52:24,320
I think he comes to work every day.

910
00:52:24,320 --> 00:52:27,200
Someone uploaded a petition saying
we should hire him back,

911
00:52:27,200 --> 00:52:29,160
and tons of people have signed it already.

912
00:52:29,160 --> 00:52:31,240
He's like a ticking bomb.

913
00:52:31,240 --> 00:52:33,840
I think we'll just have to end it
with a suspension...

914
00:52:33,840 --> 00:52:35,280
and eventually bring him back.

915
00:52:35,440 --> 00:52:36,800
You still haven't filed
his resignation letter?

916
00:52:36,800 --> 00:52:39,840
The board is very persistent
about keeping Dong-chan here.

917
00:52:39,840 --> 00:52:40,920
We can't let him leave.

918
00:52:40,920 --> 00:52:43,680
How long are you going to work
as their puppet?

919
00:52:43,680 --> 00:52:45,320
You really need to have some backbone.

920
00:52:45,760 --> 00:52:47,560
-What did you say?
-File the resignation letter.

921
00:52:47,560 --> 00:52:49,760
He wants to leave, so give him
what he wants.

922
00:52:50,720 --> 00:52:54,360
Sir, will you please just make him leave?

923
00:52:54,360 --> 00:52:56,600
Why do you want him gone so badly?

924
00:52:56,600 --> 00:52:58,000
Do you have any idea...

925
00:52:58,000 --> 00:53:01,360
how much he tainted my reputation
after he came back?

926
00:53:01,560 --> 00:53:03,480
I hate coming to work because of him.

927
00:53:03,680 --> 00:53:05,960
All the directors subtly look down on me.

928
00:53:05,960 --> 00:53:08,360
Then you should quit instead.

929
00:53:08,360 --> 00:53:11,280
How could you say that to me?
We spent years working together.

930
00:53:13,160 --> 00:53:16,560
If Dong-chan and I are drowning,
whom are you going to save first?

931
00:53:16,560 --> 00:53:18,320
I'm not capable of saving anyone.

932
00:53:18,600 --> 00:53:20,560
I'm the one who's about
to drown right now.

933
00:53:20,800 --> 00:53:23,160
But still, give me an answer.
Whom will you save first?

934
00:53:23,160 --> 00:53:25,960
Dong-chan! I'll save Dong-chan first!

935
00:53:26,600 --> 00:53:27,600
My gosh.

936
00:53:29,880 --> 00:53:31,040
It's been so long.

937
00:53:48,360 --> 00:53:51,000
(Create an account for a new channel.)

938
00:53:51,720 --> 00:53:53,000
Why don't you do this at home?

939
00:53:53,920 --> 00:53:56,560
You told them you're going to quit.
Why are you doing this here?

940
00:53:56,760 --> 00:53:57,880
Because I want to do it here.

941
00:53:58,840 --> 00:54:01,240
Are you really going to do this?

942
00:54:01,960 --> 00:54:03,760
What are you planning to do this time?

943
00:54:04,680 --> 00:54:06,560
I have a plan.

944
00:54:08,240 --> 00:54:09,320
By the way,

945
00:54:11,160 --> 00:54:13,720
there's something I haven't told you.

946
00:54:15,000 --> 00:54:17,600
But it torments me to keep it from you.

947
00:54:21,360 --> 00:54:23,840
Remember Ha-young, the girl you dated?

948
00:54:26,280 --> 00:54:30,080
She came to see me 20 years ago
after you disappeared.

949
00:54:33,480 --> 00:54:35,000
What did she say to you?

950
00:54:36,400 --> 00:54:38,840
She asked me to go to
the police station with her...

951
00:54:39,360 --> 00:54:40,680
so that they'll do an investigation.

952
00:54:41,840 --> 00:54:44,680
She told me that no one's willing
to help her out.

953
00:54:47,600 --> 00:54:48,680
But...

954
00:54:51,120 --> 00:54:52,680
I was too scared.

955
00:54:54,400 --> 00:54:55,520
So I refused.

956
00:54:58,000 --> 00:54:59,040
I'm sorry.

957
00:55:27,520 --> 00:55:28,560
Hey.

958
00:55:29,640 --> 00:55:30,720
Can we meet?

959
00:55:32,400 --> 00:55:34,360
-That won't get you anywhere.
-Exactly.

960
00:55:34,640 --> 00:55:35,680
Dong-chan.

961
00:55:36,080 --> 00:55:37,160
-Hello.
-Dong-chan.

962
00:55:37,160 --> 00:55:38,160
Hello.

963
00:55:41,040 --> 00:55:42,080
What's with him?

964
00:55:46,120 --> 00:55:47,160
What is he doing?

965
00:55:51,600 --> 00:55:53,520
I don't get it.

966
00:55:53,840 --> 00:55:55,280
This feels so wrong.

967
00:55:55,520 --> 00:55:57,680
Who would think that he quit working here?

968
00:55:58,040 --> 00:55:59,720
He's kind of like...

969
00:56:00,600 --> 00:56:02,680
those ghosts you hear
about in a girls' high school.

970
00:56:02,680 --> 00:56:04,200
He's there but he isn't.

971
00:56:04,200 --> 00:56:05,720
And he's always roaming around the place.

972
00:56:06,080 --> 00:56:07,200
What are you talking about?

973
00:56:07,520 --> 00:56:09,960
-We saw Dong-chan at the rooftop.
-The rooftop?

974
00:56:34,040 --> 00:56:35,120
Why don't you...

975
00:56:38,760 --> 00:56:40,840
ever tell me everything?

976
00:56:44,760 --> 00:56:47,520
You know what? You were always like that.

977
00:56:49,920 --> 00:56:52,120
Why didn't you tell me the truth...

978
00:56:54,840 --> 00:56:57,080
when I was busy doubting you?

979
00:57:01,520 --> 00:57:04,720
If you had told me that you tried
to confess everything to the cops...

980
00:57:09,120 --> 00:57:10,160
I waited...

981
00:57:12,160 --> 00:57:13,880
for you to tell me.

982
00:57:16,560 --> 00:57:17,760
My mom was sick.

983
00:57:18,880 --> 00:57:21,880
And I needed money, so I had no choice.

984
00:57:22,960 --> 00:57:24,080
I wanted an explanation.

985
00:57:27,120 --> 00:57:29,440
I had done so many bad things.

986
00:57:32,720 --> 00:57:35,520
And I hated myself for not having
continued to search for you.

987
00:57:38,320 --> 00:57:39,360
I...

988
00:57:45,760 --> 00:57:47,600
I thought you had abandoned me.

989
00:57:56,400 --> 00:57:57,600
Do you know what tormented me the most...

990
00:57:57,600 --> 00:57:59,040
after I woke up in 20 years?

991
00:58:00,400 --> 00:58:01,960
I wasn't bothered by how different
the world had become...

992
00:58:01,960 --> 00:58:04,120
and that the broadcasting station didn't
bother to look for me.

993
00:58:07,800 --> 00:58:09,440
It was that you didn't look for me.

994
00:58:11,320 --> 00:58:12,960
Do you know how heartbroken I was?

995
00:58:14,400 --> 00:58:16,120
Do you know how much that hurt me?

996
00:58:25,200 --> 00:58:26,920
I should've endured it.

997
00:58:29,040 --> 00:58:30,400
But I couldn't.

998
00:58:32,800 --> 00:58:34,840
And in the end, I didn't look for you.

999
00:58:36,600 --> 00:58:37,720
I gave you up...

1000
00:58:39,120 --> 00:58:40,640
for my own success.

1001
00:58:50,160 --> 00:58:51,240
Don't...

1002
00:58:55,040 --> 00:58:56,240
ever forgive me.

1003
01:00:23,240 --> 01:00:25,560
(Melting Me Softly)

1004
01:00:25,560 --> 01:00:28,120
(I know he's my destiny.)

1005
01:00:28,120 --> 01:00:30,320
(But I'm not sure if I'm his destiny.)

1006
01:00:30,600 --> 01:00:32,720
I keep getting bothered by you.

1007
01:00:32,920 --> 01:00:34,360
Are you that insecure?

1008
01:00:34,560 --> 01:00:37,000
(Do you still like him?)

1009
01:00:37,240 --> 01:00:38,520
Is there something wrong?

1010
01:00:39,360 --> 01:00:40,640
(I wonder what's up with her.)

1011
01:00:41,680 --> 01:00:44,200
(A guy named Terry Kim hasn't
gotten arrested yet.)

1012
01:00:44,520 --> 01:00:46,680
-(He ran away.)
-(I want you to do a cover on him.)

1013
01:00:46,680 --> 01:00:47,840
I'm sure you'll find something.

1014
01:00:47,960 --> 01:00:50,280
(I want you to give me the shot first.)

1015
01:00:50,640 --> 01:00:51,720
Mi-ran!

1016
01:00:51,720 --> 01:00:54,080
(Even if I ever end up
inside the capsule again,)

1017
01:00:54,080 --> 01:00:55,600
(I don't want you to follow me inside.)
